/* This is taken from projecteuler.net.
*
*If we list all the natural numbers below 10 that are multiples of 3 or 5, we get 3, 5, 6 and 9. 
*The sum of these multiples is 23.
*Find the sum of all the multiples of 3 or 5 below 1000.
*/

//I like this one because it's a good beginner's demonstration of how mod is used. 


public class EulerOne {

  public static void main(String[] args) {

    int solution = 0;

    for (int calc = 0; calc < 1000; calc++) {
    if (calc % 3 == 0 || calc % 5 == 0) {
    solution = solution + calc;
    }
    }

  System.out.println (solution);
 }

}
